Laboratory QC and Alerting Toolkit

LabPulse is a data processing system for laboratory fuel quality analysis.
It performs data cleaning, quality control (QC), outlier detection, and exposes results via a REST API and interactive dashboard.

ğŸš€ Features

-Data cleaning and validation
-Unit consistency checks (QC rules)
-IQR-based outlier detection
-Versioned processed outputs
-REST API (FastAPI)
-Interactive dashboard (Streamlit)
-Automated unit tests (pytest)

ğŸ— Architecture

Raw data (data/raw)
â†’ Pipeline (cleaning â†’ QC â†’ outliers)
â†’ Versioned outputs (data/processed/<run_id>/)
â†’ FastAPI (JSON endpoints)
â†’ Streamlit Dashboard (interactive UI)

ğŸ“¦ Installation

Clone the repository and install the project in editable mode:

pip install -e .

Optional dependencies:

pip install .[dev] # pytest
pip install .[dashboard] # streamlit + requests

âš™ï¸ Running the Pipeline

To process raw data and generate a new versioned run:

python main.py

This creates a new folder in:

data/processed/<YYYY-MM-DD_HH-MM-SS>/

Containing:

samples_cleaned.csv

alerts_outliers_iqr.csv

Each pipeline execution produces a new versioned run to preserve processing history.

ğŸŒ Running the API

Start the FastAPI server:

uvicorn labpulse.api.main:app --reload

Available endpoints:

GET /health

GET /runs/latest

GET /samples/latest

GET /alerts/latest

Interactive API documentation:

http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs

ğŸ“Š Running the Dashboard

In a separate terminal:

streamlit run dashboard.py

Dashboard runs on:

http://localhost:8501

The dashboard consumes data from the FastAPI backend.

Make sure the API server is running before launching the dashboard.

ğŸ§ª Running Tests

python -m pytest

Tests cover:

Cleaning logic

QC rule validation

Outlier detection

Pipeline execution

Data persistence

